{"title_page": "Little Company of Mary Hospital (Torrance)", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = Providence Little Company of Mary Medical Center Torrance\n| Org/Group  = Providence Health & Services\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[Torrance, California|Torrance]]\n| State      = California\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|33.8386|-118.35713|type:landmark_region:US-CA|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = Private\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = 317\n| Founded    = 1960\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = http://california.providence.org/torrance/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n|}}\n\n'''Providence Little Company of Mary Medical Center''' is a [[hospital]] in [[Torrance, California|Torrance]], [[California]], [[United States|US]].  The hospital was founded by the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]], and is part of the [[Providence Health & Services]].\n\nOn March 16, 2020, at the Beverly Hills Superior Court, a unanimous verdict was rendered against Providence Little Company of Mary Hospital in Torrance, CA for negligence in the 2014 death of a Redondo Beach man from feeding tubes placed into both of his lungs by a nurse causing both to collapse. The hospital engaged in a cover-up afterwards in trying to conceal the cause of death from the Los Angeles Coroner's Office. The California Department of Public Health Investigated and found the nurse who performed the procedure to lack documented competency in the skill. The jury awarded 1.5 million in non-economic damages to the surviving spouse.<ref>https://www.dailybreeze.com/2020/03/26/little-company-of-mary-found-negligent-in-death-of-redondo-beach-patient/</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Little Company of Mary Hospital (San Pedro)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://california.providence.org/torrance/ Little Company of Mary Hospital Official Website]\n*[http://gis.oshpd.ca.gov/atlas/places/facility/106190470 This hospital in the CA Healthcare Atlas] A project by OSHPD\n*[https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/nurse-killed-patient-73-shoving-feeding-tube-lungs-instead-stomach-12460433/ Malpractice Case]\n*[https://www.dailybreeze.com/2020/03/26/little-company-of-mary-found-negligent-in-death-of-redondo-beach-patient/ Malpractice Case]\n\n{{Torrance, California}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Los Angeles County, California]]\n[[Category:Providence Health & Services]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Torrance, California]]\n[[Category:Hospitals established in 1960]]\n[[Category:1960 establishments in California]]\n\n\n{{California-hospital-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{More references|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox Hospital\n| Name       = Providence Little Company of Mary Medical Center Torrance\n| Org/Group  = Providence Health & Services\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[Torrance, California|Torrance]]\n| State      = California\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|33.8386|-118.35713|type:landmark_region:US-CA|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = Private\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = 317\n| Founded    = 1960\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = http://california.providence.org/torrance/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n|}}\n\n'''Providence Little Company of Mary Medical Center''' is a [[hospital]] in [[Torrance, California|Torrance]], [[California]], [[United States|US]].  The hospital was founded by the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]], and is part of the [[Providence Health & Services]].\n\nOn March 16, 2020, at the Beverly Hills Superior Court, a unanimous verdict was rendered against Providence Little Company of Mary Hospital in Torrance, CA for negligence in the 2014 death of a Redondo Beach man from feeding tubes placed into both of his lungs by a nurse causing both to collapse. The hospital engaged in a cover-up afterwards in trying to conceal the cause of death from the Los Angeles Coroner's Office. The California Department of Public Health Investigated and found the nurse who performed the procedure to lack documented competency in the skill. The jury awarded 1.5 million in non-economic damages to the surviving spouse.<ref>https://www.dailybreeze.com/2020/03/26/little-company-of-mary-found-negligent-in-death-of-redondo-beach-patient/</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Little Company of Mary Hospital (San Pedro)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://california.providence.org/torrance/ Little Company of Mary Hospital Official Website]\n*[http://gis.oshpd.ca.gov/atlas/places/facility/106190470 This hospital in the CA Healthcare Atlas] A project by OSHPD\n*[https://metro.co.uk/2020/03/26/nurse-killed-patient-73-shoving-feeding-tube-lungs-instead-stomach-12460433/ Malpractice Case]\n*[https://www.dailybreeze.com/2020/03/26/little-company-of-mary-found-negligent-in-death-of-redondo-beach-patient/ Malpractice Case]\n\n{{Torrance, California}}\n\n[[Category:Hospitals in Los Angeles County, California]]\n[[Category:Providence Health & Services]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Torrance, California]]\n[[Category:Hospitals established in 1960]]\n[[Category:1960 establishments in California]]\n\n\n{{California-hospital-stub}}\n", 