{"title_page": "Little Company of Mary Hospital (San Pedro)", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = Little Company of Mary Hospital\n| Org/Group  = Providence Health & Services\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[San Pedro, Los Angeles, California|San Pedro]]\n| State      = California\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|33.73831|-118.30507|type:landmark_region:US-CA|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = non-profit\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = 587\n| Founded    = 1925\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = http://california.providence.org/san-pedro/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n|}}\n\n'''Little Company of Mary Hospital''' is a [[hospital]] in [[San Pedro, Los Angeles, California|San Pedro]], [[California]], [[United States|USA]].  The hospital was founded in 1909 by Mrs. Lillian B. Mullen, a graduate nurse and physician from New York. The hospital began in the old Clarence Hotel. The first building constructed for the hospital was located on Sixth St. and was dedicated in 1925. Throughout its history, the hospital has been through numerous remodeling and construction projects and several name changes. The hospital aligned with the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]] in the early 1990s. The affiliation with the Sisters of Providence took place in 1998 and the hospital (now medical center) is currently a part of [[Providence Health & Services]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Little Company of Mary Hospital (Torrance)]]\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://california.providence.org/san-pedro/ Little Company of Mary Hospital Official Website]\n*[http://gis.oshpd.ca.gov/atlas/places/facility/106190680 This hospital in the CA Healthcare Atlas] A project by OSHPD\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1925]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Providence Health & Services]]\n[[Category:San Pedro, Los Angeles]]\n\n\n{{California-hospital-stub}}\n{{LosAngeles-struct-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=May 2019}}\n{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = Little Company of Mary Hospital\n| Org/Group  = Providence Health & Services\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[San Pedro, Los Angeles, California|San Pedro]]\n| State      = California\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|33.73831|-118.30507|type:landmark_region:US-CA|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = non-profit\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = 587\n| Founded    = 1925\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = http://california.providence.org/san-pedro/\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n|}}\n\n'''Little Company of Mary Hospital''' is a [[hospital]] in [[San Pedro, Los Angeles, California|San Pedro]], [[California]], [[United States|USA]].  The hospital was founded in 1909 by Mrs. Lillian B. Mullen, a graduate nurse and physician from New York. The hospital began in the old Clarence Hotel. The first building constructed for the hospital was located on Sixth St. and was dedicated in 1925. Throughout its history, the hospital has been through numerous remodeling and construction projects and several name changes. The hospital aligned with the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]] in the early 1990s. The affiliation with the Sisters of Providence took place in 1998 and the hospital (now medical center) is currently a part of [[Providence Health & Services]].\n\n==See also==\n*[[Little Company of Mary Hospital (Torrance)]]\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://california.providence.org/san-pedro/ Little Company of Mary Hospital Official Website]\n*[http://gis.oshpd.ca.gov/atlas/places/facility/106190680 This hospital in the CA Healthcare Atlas] A project by OSHPD\n\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1925]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Providence Health & Services]]\n[[Category:San Pedro, Los Angeles]]\n\n\n{{California-hospital-stub}}\n{{LosAngeles-struct-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_Company_of_Mary_Hospital_(San_Pedro)"}
{"title_page": "Little Company of Mary Hospital (Evergreen Park)", "text_new": "{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = OSF Little Company of Mary Medical Center\n| Org/Group  = OSF HealthCare\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[Evergreen Park, Illinois|Evergreen Park]]\n| State      = Illinois\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|41.72145|-87.69294|type:landmark_region:US-IL|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = Private\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = \n| Founded    = 1930\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = {{URL|www.lcmh.org}}\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -->\n|}}\n\n'''OSF Little Company of Mary Medical Center''' is a [[hospital]] in [[Evergreen Park, Illinois]], [[United States|USA]].  The hospital was founded on January 19, 1930 by the [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]]<ref>[http://www.lcmh.org/ Little Company of Mary Hospital, Evergreen Park, IL<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and serves much of the southwest side of Chicago. On October 17, 2019, [[OSF HealthCare]] signed a merger agreement with Little Company of Mary Hospital. The merger took place on February 1, 2020.<ref>https://revcycleintelligence.com/news/osf-little-company-of-mary-take-next-hospital-merger-step</ref>\n\nThe first human organ transplant (kidney) was performed here in 1950 on a 44-year-old woman who had [[polycystic kidney disease]].<ref name=dsun>{{cite news|first=Nicole C.|last=Brambila|title=Kidney transplant pioneer James West dies in Palm Desert |url=http://www.mydesert.com/article/20120801/NEWS01/208010323/Kidney-transplant-pioneer-James-West-dies-Palm-Desert |work=[[The Desert Sun]] |publisher= |date=2011-08-01 |accessdate=2012-08-20}}</ref><ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20020701075140/http://www.lcmh.org/body.cfm?id=20 Little Company of Mary Hospital, Evergreen Park, IL]</ref>\n\n==Deaths==\n*[[Mahalia Jackson]] (1911\u20131972).<ref>{{cite news |author=Alden Whitman |title=Mahalia Jackson, Gospel Singer and a Civil Rights Symbol, Dies  |url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=9E02E6D7163EE63ABC4051DFB7668389669EDE |quote=Mahalia Jackson, who rose from Deep South poverty to world renown as a passionate gospel singer, died of a heart seizure yesterday in Little Company of Mary Hospital in Evergreen Park, Ill., a Chicago suburb. |newspaper=[[New York Times]] |date=January 28, 1972 |accessdate=2014-12-15 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references />\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.lcmh.org/ Little Company of Mary Hospital Official Website]\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Hospital buildings completed in 1930]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Evergreen Park, Illinois]]\n[[Category:Hospitals in Cook County, Illinois]]\n\n\n{{Illinois-hospital-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox hospital\n| Name       = OSF Little Company of Mary Medical Center\n| Org/Group  = OSF HealthCare\n| Image      = <!-- optional -->\n| Caption    = <!-- optional -->\n| Logo       = \n| Location   = \n| Region     = [[Evergreen Park, Illinois|Evergreen Park]]\n| State      = Illinois\n| Country    = US\n| coordinates= {{Coord|41.72145|-87.69294|type:landmark_region:US-IL|display=inline,title}}\n| HealthCare = Private\n| Type       = Community\n| Speciality = <!-- if devoted to a speciality, i.e. not if has broad spectrum of specialities -->\n| Standards  = <!-- optional if no national standards -->\n| Emergency  = <!-- UK/IR/HK/SG: Yes/No, CA/US: I/II/III for Trauma certification level -->\n| Affiliation= None\n| Beds       = \n| Founded    = 1930\n| Closed     = <!-- optional -->\n| Website    = {{URL|www.lcmh.org}}\n| Wiki-Links = <!-- optional -