   &ndash; [[Dion DiMucci]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1939   &ndash; [[Jerry Moore (American football, born 1939)|Jerry Moore]], American football player and coach\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[James Brolin]], American actor\n*  1940   &ndash; [[Joe Torre]], American baseball player and manager\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Frank Farian]], German songwriter and producer\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Lonnie Mack]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 2016)\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Martha Reeves]], American singer and politician \n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Giacinto Facchetti]], Italian footballer (d. 2006)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Adolf Ogi]], Swiss politician, 84th [[President of the Swiss Confederation]]\n*[[1943]] &ndash; [[Joseph J. Ellis]], American historian and author\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[David Hemery]], English hurdler and author<ref>{{cite book|author=Amateur Athletic Union of the United States|title=Amateur Athlete|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=iIkqAAAAMAAJ|year=1967|publisher=Amateur Athletic Union of the United States|page=13}}</ref>\n*[[1945]] &ndash; [[Pat Doherty]], Irish Republican politician\n*[[1946]] &ndash; [[Kalpana Mohan]], Indian actress\n*  1946   &ndash;  [[John Naughton]], Scottish-Irish journalist, author, and academic\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Steve Forbes]], American publisher and politician\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Carlos Col\u00f3n Sr.]], Puerto Rican-American wrestler and promoter\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Jeanne C\u00f3rdova]], American journalist and activist (d. 2016)\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Graham Spanier]], 16th President of [[Pennsylvania State University]]\n*  1948   &ndash; [[Hartmut Michel]], German biochemist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[Dennis Lillee]], Australian cricketer and coach\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Richard Branson]], English businessman, founded [[Virgin Group]]\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Jack Dongarra]], American computer scientist and academic\n*  1950   &ndash; [[Kostas Eleftherakis]], G