 Button]], American figure skater and actor\n*  1929   &ndash; [[Screamin' Jay Hawkins]], American R&B singer-songwriter, musician, and actor (d. 2000) \n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[Robert Ellis Miller]], American director and screenwriter\n*[[1933]] &ndash; [[Jean Yanne]], French actor, director, producer, and screenwriter (d. 2003)\n*  1933   &ndash; [[Yevgeny Yevtushenko]], Russian poet and playwright (d. 2017)\n*[[1934]] &ndash; [[Edward Bond]], English director, playwright, and screenwriter\n*  1934   &ndash; [[Darlene Conley]], American actress (d. 2007)\n*[[1935]] &ndash; [[Tenley Albright]], American figure skater and physician\n*  1935   &ndash; [[Jayendra Saraswathi]], Indian guru, 69th [[Shankaracharya]]\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Roald Hoffmann]], Polish chemist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Chemistry|Nobel Prize]] laureate\n*  1937   &ndash; [[Hunter S. Thompson]], American journalist and author (d. 2005)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[John Connelly (footballer)|John Connelly]], English footballer (d. 2012)\n*  1938   &ndash; [[Ian Stewart (musician)|Ian Stewart]], Scottish keyboard player and manager (d. 1985)\n*  1938   &ndash; [[Paul Verhoeven]], Dutch director, producer, and screenwriter\n*[[1939]] &ndash; [[Brian Auger]], English rock and jazz keyboard player \n*  1939   &ndash; [[Dion DiMucci]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist \n*  1939   &ndash; [[Jerry Moore (American football, born 1939)|Jerry Moore]], American football player and coach\n*[[1940]] &ndash; [[James Brolin]], American actor\n*  1940   &ndash; [[Joe Torre]], American baseball player and manager\n*[[1941]] &ndash; [[Frank Farian]], German songwriter and producer\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Lonnie Mack]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (d. 2016)\n*  1941   &ndash; [[Martha Reeves]], American singer and politician \n*[[1942]] &ndash; [[Giacinto Facchetti]], Italian footballer (d. 2006)\n*  1942   &ndash; [[Adolf Ogi]], Swiss politician, 84th [[President of the Swiss Confederation]]\n*[[1943]] &n