gos]], Greek footballer\n*  1985   &ndash; [[James Norton (actor)|James Norton]], English actor\n*[[1986]] &ndash; [[Natalia Mikhailova]], Russian ice dancer\n*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Tontowi Ahmad]], Indonesian badminton player<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.olympic.org/tontowi-ahmad|title=Tontowi Ahmad|website=Olympics|access-date=5 December 2019}}</ref>\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[\u00c4nis Ben-Hatira]], German-Tunisian footballer\n*  1988   &ndash; [[C\u00e9sar Villaluz]], Mexican footballer\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Jamie Benn]], Canadian ice hockey player\n*  1989   &ndash; [[Sebastian Mielitz]], German footballer\n*  1989   &ndash; [[Yohan Mollo]], French footballer\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Nabil Fekir]], French footballer\n*[[1993]] &ndash; [[Lee Tae-min]], South Korean singer and actor\n*  1993   &ndash; [[Michael Lichaa]], Australian rugby league player\n*[[1994]] &ndash; [[Nilo Soares]], East Timorese footballer\n*[[1997]] &ndash; [[Noah Lyles]], American sprinter<ref>{{cite web |title=Noah Lyles|url=https://www.worldathletics.org/athletes/united-states/noah-lyles-284369|publisher=World Athletics|accessdate=7 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n<!-- Do not add people without Wikipedia articles to this list. Do not trust \u201cthis year in history\u201d websites for accurate date information. Do not link multiple occurrences of the same year, just link the first occurrence. -->\n\n==Deaths==\n* [[AD 707|707]] &ndash; [[Emperor Monmu]] of Japan (b. 683)\n* [[715]] &ndash; [[Muhammad bin Qasim]], Umayyad general (b. 695)\n* [[912]] &ndash; [[Zhu Wen]], Chinese emperor (b. 852)\n* [[924]] &ndash; [[Abu'l-Hasan Ali ibn al-Furat]], Abbasid vizier (b. 855)\n* [[928]] &ndash; [[Stephen II of Constantinople|Stephen II]], patriarch of [[Constantinople]]\n* [[984]] &ndash; [[Dietrich I of Metz|Dietrich I]], bishop of [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Metz|Metz]]<ref name=\"theo\">{{cite web |title=Theoderich I. von Metz |url=https://www.heiligenlexikon.de/BiographienD/Dietrich_von_Metz.html |website=hei