phy & Novels |url=https://www.britannica.com/biography/Jane-Austen |website=Encyclopedia Britannica |accessdate=11 January 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n*[[1837]] &ndash; [[Vincenzo Borg]], Maltese merchant and rebel leader (b. 1777)\n*[[1863]] &ndash; [[Robert Gould Shaw]], American colonel (b. 1837)\n*[[1872]] &ndash; [[Benito Ju\u00e1rez]], Mexican lawyer and politician, 26th [[President of Mexico]] (b. 1806)\n*[[1884]] &ndash; [[Ferdinand von Hochstetter]], Austrian geologist and academic (b. 1829)\n*[[1887]] &ndash; [[Dorothea Dix]], American social reformer and activist (b. 1802)\n*[[1890]] &ndash; [[Lydia Becker]], English journalist, author, and activist, co-founded the ''[[Women's Suffrage Journal]]'' (b. 1827)\n*[[1892]] &ndash; [[Thomas Cook]], English travel agent, founded the [[Thomas Cook Group]] (b. 1808)\n*[[1899]] &ndash; [[Horatio Alger]], American novelist and journalist (b. 1832)\n*[[1916]] &ndash; [[Benjamin C. Truman]], American journalist and author (b. 1835)\n*[[1925]] &ndash; [[Louis-Nazaire B\u00e9gin]], Canadian cardinal (b. 1840)\n*[[1932]] &ndash; [[Jean Jules Jusserand]], French author and diplomat, [[List of French ambassadors to the United States|French Ambassador to the United States]] (b. 1855)\n*[[1937]] &ndash; [[Julian Bell]], English poet and academic (b. 1908)\n*[[1938]] &ndash; [[Marie of Romania]] (b. 1875)\n*[[1944]] &ndash; [[Thomas Sturge Moore]], English author, poet, and playwright (b. 1870)\n*[[1947]] &ndash; [[Evald Tipner]], Estonian footballer and ice hockey player (b. 1906)\n*[[1948]] &ndash; [[Herman Gummerus]], Finnish historian, academic, and politician (b. 1877)\n*[[1949]] &ndash; [[V\u00edt\u011bzslav Nov\u00e1k]], Czech composer and educator (b. 1870)\n*  1949   &ndash; [[Francisco Javier Arana]], Guatemalan Army colonel and briefly Guatemalan head of state (b.1905)\n*[[1950]] &ndash; [[Carl Clinton Van Doren]], American critic and biographer (b. 1885)\n*[[1952]] &ndash; [[Paul Saintenoy]], Belgian architect and historian (b. 1862)\n*[[1954]] &ndash; [[Machine Gun Kelly]], American gangster (b. 1895)\n*[[1966]] &ndash; [[Bobby Fuller]], American singer-songwriter and guitarist (b. 1942)\n*[[1968]] &ndash; [[Corneille Heymans]], Belgian physiologist and academic, [[Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine|Nobel Prize]] laureate (b. 1892)\n*[[1969]] &ndash; [[Mary Jo Kopechne]], American educator and secretary (b. 1940)\n*[[1973]] &ndash; [[Jack Hawkins]], English actor (b. 1910)\n*[[1975]] &ndash; [[Vaughn Bod\u0113]], American illustrator (b. 1941)\n*[[1981]] &ndash; [[Sonja Branting-Westerst\u00e5hl]], Swedish lawyer (b. 1890)<ref>{{cite book|last=Harnesk|first=Paul|title=Vem \u00e4r Vem?|location=Stockholm|publisher=Vem \u00e4r Vem Bokf\u00f6rlag|year=1945|url=http://runeberg.org/vemarvem/sthlm45/0131.html|accessdate=6 September 2019}}</ref>\n*[[1982]] &ndash; [[Roman Jakobson]], Russian\u2013American linguist and theorist (b. 1896)\n*[[1984]] &ndash; [[Lally Bowers]], English actress (b. 1914)\n*  1984   &ndash; [[Grigori Kromanov]], Estonian director and screenwriter (b. 1926)\n*[[1987]] &ndash; [[Gilberto Freyre]], Brazilian sociologist, anthropologist, historian, writer, painter, journalist and congressman (b. 1907)\n*[[1988]] &ndash; [[Nico]], German singer-songwriter, keyboard player, and actress (b. 1938)\n*  1988   &ndash; [[Joly Braga Santos]], Portuguese composer and conductor (b. 1924)\n*[[1989]] &ndash; [[Donnie Moore]], American baseball player (b. 1954)\n*  1989   &ndash; [[Rebecca Schaeffer]], American model and actress (b.1967)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.franksreelreviews.com/shorttakes/shaeffer/shaeffer.htm|last=Williams|first=Frank|title=The Stalking Death that Changed the Law: Rebecca Schaeffer Never Lived to Realize Her Success|website=frankseelreviews.com|accessdate=20 July 2019}}</ref>\n*[[1990]] &ndash; [[Karl Menninger]], American psychiatrist and author (b. 1896)\n*  1990   &ndash; [[Yun Posun]], South Korean politician, 2nd [[President of South K